German Cache Coherence — Proof Strategy
========================================

This document describes the recommended proof structure for
Leslie/Examples/CacheCoherence/GermanMessages/, the message-level
German cache coherence protocol.

See also: docs/proof-strategy-help.md for general patterns.

---

TARGET INVARIANT
----------------

The safety property to prove is:

  invariant n s  =  ctrlProp n s ∧ dataProp n s

where:
  ctrlProp: at most one exclusive holder; shared and exclusive are disjoint
  dataProp: memory matches auxData when no exclusive grant outstanding;
            all valid cache copies match auxData

The strengthened inductive invariant needed is strongInvariant (10 conjuncts)
plus several auxiliary channel/bookkeeping predicates.


RECOMMENDED FILE STRUCTURE
---------------------------

Leslie/Examples/CacheCoherence/GermanMessages/
  Model.lean           -- MState, MAction as named predicates, next, init, spec
  FrameLemmas.lean     -- Per-action frame theorems (what each action does NOT change)
  Invariant.lean       -- Invariant definitions grouped by read-footprint
  InitProof.lean       -- fullStrongInvariant holds for init states
  StepProof.lean       -- fullStrongInvariant preserved by each action
  Theorem.lean         -- Reachable, germanMessages_invariant main theorem


ACTION MODIFICATION FOOTPRINTS
-------------------------------

Use these to determine which invariant groups are trivially preserved.

  sendReqS(i)    : writes chan1[i].cmd only
  sendReqE(i)    : writes chan1[i].cmd only
  recvReqS(i)    : writes chan1[i].cmd, curCmd, curPtr, invSet (= shrSet)
  recvReqE(i)    : writes chan1[i].cmd, curCmd, curPtr, invSet (= shrSet)
  sendInv(i)     : writes chan2[i].cmd, invSet[i]
  sendInvAck(i)  : writes chan2[i].cmd, chan3[i].{cmd,data}, cache[i].state
  recvInvAck(i)  : writes chan3[i].cmd, shrSet[i], exGntd, memData (if exGntd)
  sendGntS(i)    : writes chan2[i].{cmd,data}, shrSet[i], curCmd
  sendGntE(i)    : writes chan2[i].{cmd,data}, shrSet[i], exGntd, curCmd
  recvGntS(i)    : writes cache[i].{state,data}, chan2[i].cmd
  recvGntE(i)    : writes cache[i].{state,data}, chan2[i].cmd
  store(i,d)     : writes cache[i].data, auxData


INVARIANT GROUPING BY READ-FOOTPRINT
--------------------------------------

Group A — reads only chan2, chan3:
  grantExcludesInvAck : chan2[i]=gntE → chan3[i]≠invAck
  gntSExcludesInvAck  : chan2[i]=gntS → chan3[i]≠invAck
  invAckClearsGrant   : chan3[i]=invAck → chan2[i]=empty
  chan3IsInvAck        : chan3[i] ∈ {empty, invAck}
  Preserved trivially by: sendReqS, sendReqE, recvReqS, recvReqE, store
  Non-trivial for: sendInv, sendInvAck, recvInvAck, sendGntS, sendGntE, recvGntS, recvGntE

Group B — reads cache, shrSet, exGntd:
  exclusiveSelfClean       : cache[i]=E → chan2[i]∉{gntS,gntE} ∧ chan3[i]≠invAck
  cacheInShrSet            : cache[i]≠I → shrSet[i]=true
  noExclusiveWhenFalse     : exGntd=false → ∀i, cache[i]≠E ∧ chan2[i]≠gntE
  exclusiveImpliesExGntd   : cache[i]=E ∨ chan2[i]=gntE → exGntd=true
  noSharedWhenExGntd       : exGntd=true → ∀i, cache[i]≠S ∧ chan2[i]≠gntS
  Preserved trivially by: sendReqS, sendReqE, sendInv (mostly)

Group C — reads curCmd, invSet, exGntd:
  invRequiresNonEmpty : chan2[i]=inv → curCmd≠empty
  invClearsInvSet     : chan2[i]=inv → invSet[i]=false
  invSetImpliesClean  : invSet[i]=true → chan3[i]=empty
  invSetSubsetShrSet  : invSet[i]=true → shrSet[i]=true
  Preserved trivially by: sendReqS, sendReqE, recvGntS, recvGntE, store

Group D — core safety invariant:
  ctrlProp  : E→others are I; S→others are I or S
  dataProp  : memData=auxData when !exGntd; cache[i].data=auxData when cache[i]≠I
  grantDataProp      : chan2[i]∈{gntS,gntE} → chan2[i].data=auxData
  invAckDataProp     : exGntd=true ∧ chan3[i]=invAck → chan3[i].data=auxData
  uniqueShrSetWhenExGntd: exGntd=true → shrSet has at most one true entry
  chanImpliesShrSet  : any non-empty msg in chan2[i] or chan3[i] → shrSet[i]=true
  exGntdWitness      : exGntd=true → ∃j, cache[j]=E ∨ chan2[j]=gntE ∨ chan3[j]=invAck


FRAME LEMMA TEMPLATES (FrameLemmas.lean)
-----------------------------------------

For each action, prove one lemma of this form and mark @[simp]:

  @[simp] lemma sendReqS_frame (h : s' = { s with chan1 := ... }) :
      s'.cache = s.cache ∧ s'.chan2 = s.chan2 ∧ s'.chan3 = s.chan3 ∧
      s'.invSet = s.invSet ∧ s'.shrSet = s.shrSet ∧
      s'.exGntd = s.exGntd ∧ s'.curCmd = s.curCmd ∧
      s'.memData = s.memData ∧ s'.auxData = s.auxData := by
    subst h; exact ⟨rfl, rfl, rfl, rfl, rfl, rfl, rfl, rfl, rfl⟩

For actions that modify multiple fields, use field-specific equalities:

  @[simp] lemma sendInv_frame_cache (h : sendInv_step s s' i) : s'.cache = s.cache
  @[simp] lemma sendInv_frame_chan3 (h : sendInv_step s s' i) : s'.chan3 = s.chan3
  -- etc.

Then group-level preservation becomes:

  lemma groupA_preserved_sendReqS (h : sendReqS_step s s' i) (hg : groupA n s) :
      groupA n s' := by simp_all [groupA, sendReqS_frame h]


NON-TRIVIAL CASES (the actual interesting proofs)
--------------------------------------------------

These are the ~15 sub-goals that require real reasoning:

1. sendInvAck preserves dataProp.invAckDataProp
   (case: cache[i]=E vs cache[i]≠E, uses exGntdWitness)

2. sendInvAck preserves grantDataProp
   (data conditional on cache state)

3. recvInvAck preserves ctrlProp (exGntd=true branch: all caches become I)

4. recvInvAck preserves dataProp (memData updated from chan3[i].data)

5. sendGntE preserves uniqueShrSetWhenExGntd
   (only i in shrSet: uses ∀j, shrSet j = false precondition)

6. sendGntE preserves exGntdWitness
   (witnessed by i via chan2[i]=gntE)

7. recvGntE preserves noSharedWhenExGntd
   (cache[i] was I before grant, others unchanged)

8. recvGntE preserves exGntdWitness
   (cache[i] now E, was previously gntE)

9. store preserves dataProp
   (auxData updated, cache[i].data updated, all other valid caches must
    have been I or must still match — requires exclusiveSelfClean)

10. recvGntS preserves ctrlProp
    (exGntd=false, so no exclusive holder; shared is fine)

11. sendGntS preserves grantDataProp
    (data = memData = auxData, since exGntd=false implies memData=auxData)

12. recvInvAck (exGntd=false branch) preserves all group-B predicates
    (shrSet[i] cleared, exGntd unchanged)


PROOF TEMPLATE FOR StepProof.lean
-----------------------------------

  private theorem fullInvariant_preserved
      {n : Nat} {s s' : MState n}
      (hs : fullInvariant n s)
      (hstep : Next n s s') :
      fullInvariant n s' := by
    obtain ⟨hcore, hchannel, hcache, hcontrol⟩ := hs
    rcases hstep with
      | ⟨i, h⟩ =>  -- sendReqS
        exact ⟨by simpa [sendReqS_frame h] using hcore,
               by simp [sendReqS_frame h, hchannel],
               by simp [sendReqS_frame h, hcache],
               by simp [sendReqS_frame h, hcontrol]⟩
      | ...      -- sendInvAck: use explicit case analysis
        ...

Each trivial case is 4 lines; each non-trivial case is 10-30 lines.
Total expected length: ~400 lines for StepProof.lean.


NOTES ON EXISTING CODE
-----------------------

The file Leslie/Examples/CacheCoherence/GermanMessages.lean contains:
- A working model (MState, MAction, next, init)
- Proved init cases (germanMessages_init_* theorems)
- Proved strongInvariant preservation for all 12 actions (strongInvariant_preserved_*)
- The fullStrongInvariant definition (which this strategy calls fullInvariant)
- Missing: frame lemmas, group-level preservation, main inductive theorem

When building GermanMessages/, extract the model from GermanMessages.lean into
Model.lean unchanged, then build the proof infrastructure on top.
